<HEAD>Lawyer Fined More Than $100,000 In Divorce Case</HEAD>
<DATELINE>MACON, Ga. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A judge ordered a lawyer to pay more than
$100,000 to a man who remarried erroneously believing his divorce
was final.
   Alvin C. McDougald, 34, of Fort Valley, apparently never filed
the divorce petition of Bobby Eugene Wood.
   Judge Bryant Culpepper said McDougald's actions had been
``fraudulent'' and were ``intentional, willful, wanton and were
taken without regard to the consequences'' to Wood.
   Culpepper on Monday ordered McDougald to pay Wood $50,000 in
punitive damages, $50,000 to compensate Wood for mental suffering
and $2,875 in actual damages.
