<FIRST>d a PM-BRF--Car-House     04-25 0181</FIRST>
<SECOND>PM-BRF--Car-House,0186</SECOND>
<HEAD>Car Smashes Through House, Misses Sleeping Couple</HEAD>
<DATELINE>KINGSTON, Mass. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A sports car crashed into a house and
tore through a bedroom but missed the couple sleeping there.
   The car left the street at about 1:30 a.m. Sunday, ran up a
small embankment and hurtled through the air. It glanced off a
pickup truck parked outside the house, crashed through the house
and landed about 35 feet away in a yard next door.
   ``All I heard was a big explosion and glass smashing and the
wall came in and fell on me,'' said Ronald Viator, the owner of the
house. ``If they hadn't hit my pickup, they would have come through
the wall and landed on top of my wife and me.''
   The driver of the car was taken to Jordan Hospital in Plymouth
with cuts and bruises and released. A passenger suffered a broken
breastbone.
   Viator and his wife, Ann, escaped serious injury. Their
children, 9-year-old Jennifer and 5-year-old Jessica, were asleep
in their bedroom in a far corner of the house and were not injured.
</TEXT>
