<HEAD>San Jose Teachers on Strike</HEAD>
<DATELINE>SAN JOSE, Calif. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Hundreds of teachers staged a one-day
strike today against the San Jose Unified School District, which
has 29,000 students in 40 schools.
   The main reason for the strike was that the district ``has
refused to return to the bargaining table,'' said Brian McKenna,
executive director of the 1,569-member San Jose Teachers
