<FILEID>AP-NR-04-25-89 1216EST</FILEID>
<FIRST>r w PM-Bush-Texas     04-25 0130</FIRST>
<SECOND>PM-Bush-Texas,120</SECOND>
<HEAD>President Declares Storm Disaster for Texas</HEAD>
<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   President Bush today declared a federal
disaster in Texas, where thunderstorms and flooding destroyed
property in late March.
   Bush's declaration frees federal funds for such assistance as
temporary housing and grants and low-interest loans for individuals
and businesses hard hit by the storms in the western part of the
state.
   The federal aid also will go to local governments to repair
public facilities, paying up to 75 percent of the cost.
   The Federal Emergency Management Agency will make the assistance
available to the Texas counties of Cass, Cherokee, Gregg, Harrison,
Marion and Rusk, with coordination of the efforts centered in
Denton.
   The White House announced the declaration in Washington and in
San Jose, Calif., where Bush was traveling.
</TEXT>
</DOC>
