<HEAD>Soviet Seaman Jumps into the Sea, Seeks Asylum</HEAD>
<DATELINE>COPENHAGEN, Denmark (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A Soviet seaman who jumped ship into
near-freezing water off the Danish coast was rescued and placed in
a refugee camp, the naval command headquarters said Tuesday.
   The 26-year-old sailor donned a life-vest and jumped overboard
Saturday from a Soviet civilian vessel heading north through the
Great Belt strait on its way to the North Sea, the command said.
   A passing Danish navy ship spotted the seaman and picked him up.
He was turned over to police at the port of Korsoer, where he asked
for political asylum.
   The man, who was not identified, was lodged in a refugee center
to await a decision, the navy said.
