<HEAD>Controversial Talk Show Host Downey Attacked</HEAD>
<HEAD>Eds: Leads with 12 grafs with comment from police about lack of corroboration.
Picks up 9th graf `About the...'</HEAD>
<DATELINE>SAN FRANCISCO (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Three youths attacked Morton Downey Jr. in
an airport bathroom, cutting off some of his hair and painting a
swastika on his head, said the controversial TV talk show host.
   ``They sieg heiled me when they left,'' Downey told television
station KOFY after Monday night's incident at San Francisco
International Airport.
   Downey said one of the youths ``got me from behind, another got
me around the neck, one sat on me.''
   Downey said he was not injured and did not go to a hospital. He
was in San Francisco to promote his television show on KOFY.
   ``I think I kicked one of them,'' Downey said. ``At least I hope
I did.''
   Airport spokesman Ron Wilson said police are investigating
Downey's report.
   He said officers and medical crews were called for help and
found Downey already in the back of his limousine.
   A man who was in the restroom at the same time as Downey told
investigators he did not see any confrontation, Wilson said. ``The
only thing that he saw was he did see Mr. Downey walk briskly out
of the restroom, assisted by a couple of young men who had been
with him. They were friends of Downey who had traveled in the
limousine with him.''
   In an interview at his San Francisco hotel room early Tuesday,
Downey said he thought his attackers were ``skinheads'' such as the
young racists represented and reviled on Downey's program.
   ``It's the skinheads, the same ones who have threatened me for
so long,'' he said, discounting the chance his assailants were from
San Francisco's gay community, which has been critical of his
frequent tirades against homosexuals.
   Ed Walsh, KOFY's news assignment editor, said only a small
portion of Downey's hair was cut.
   ``It looks like something a little kid would do to another
little kid,'' he said. ``Kind of like a bald spot. I think it was
done with scissors and the swastika was made with a marker pen.''
   About the same time as Downey said the assault occurred, a bomb
threat forced KOFY to go off the air during the time slot for the
syndicated series ``The Morton Downey Jr. Show.''
   The nature of the threat was not explained. The show _ scheduled
to begin at 11 p.m. _ returned at 11:35 p.m.
   The show was making its first appearance in San Francisco since
it was canceled last summer in response to protests by local gay
activist organizations.
