<HEAD>Tass Reduces Death Toll From Landslides To 29</HEAD>
<DATELINE>MOSCOW (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Tass said Tuesday that 29 people were killed by
mudslides in a mountainous area near the Turkish border last week.
   Radio Moscow had reported Friday that 52 people perished when
landslides buried four houses and a bus in the mountains of
Adzharia in the southern republic of Georgia.
   The report by the official Tass agency did not refer to the
previous casualty figures but indicated some of the people feared
killed had survived.
   It quoted geologists in the area as saying that because of rains
the situation ``remains extreme and landslides and mud torrents can
go on the attack again at any moment.''
   The agency said slides have forced more than 3,000 families from
their homes and military helicopters are helping evacuate the
victims and distriblute supplies being contributed from throughout
the Soviet Union.
