<HEAD>Mexican Agents Seize 1,760 Pounds of Cocaine; Arrest 12</HEAD>
<DATELINE>MEXICO CITY (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Federal agents seized 1,760 pounds of cocaine
during raids in northern Mexico and arrested 12 people suspected of
planning to smuggle the drug into the United States, prosecutors
said Tuesday.
   The attorney general's office, which provided details in a
statement, said police are also looking for two pilots, a Mexican
and a Colombian. They are suspected of flying the drug into Mexico
from the Colombian city of Barranquilla.
