<FIRST>r a AM-HouseExplosion     04-25 0174</FIRST>
<SECOND>AM-House Explosion,0177</SECOND>
<UNK>Woman Critically Injured in Explosion</UNK>
<DATELINE>VINCENNES, Ind. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   An explosion Tuesday demolished a house,
critically injuring a woman inside, and damaged 11 other homes,
authorities said.
   The 3:26 a.m. blast was felt up to five miles away. It carried
debris half a block away from the demolished house and shattered
windows and cracked walls in neighboring homes.
   Norma McMahan, 64, of Fort Wayne, who was staying in the
one-story, frame house, was found in what was left of the garage,
although it was unclear where she was at the time of the explosion,
authorities said. Firefighters had to pry a section of the roof off
of her.
   Mrs. McMahan was in critical condition Tuesday evening in the
burn unit of Wishard Hospital in Indianapolis, where she was rushed
by helicopter. She suffered cuts and burns over most of her body.
   Firefighters extinguished two small fires at the demolished
home. One outside wall of the home was left standing.
   Authorities strongly suspected natural gas as the cause of the
explosion.
</TEXT>
