<FIRST>u f PM-BoeingOrder     04-25 0193</FIRST>
<SECOND>PM-Boeing Order,0198</SECOND>
<HEAD>USAir Places Boeing Jet Order for Up to $1.7 Billion</HEAD>
<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   USAir Group Inc. has ordered 18 Boeing 737
jets and taken options on 36 more in a transaction valued at up to
$1.7 billion, the airline announced today.
   The aircraft will be in the 737-300, -400 or -500 series.
Deliveries of the 18 firm orders will be one a month during 1991
and two monthly during the first quarter of 1992, with options
possibly exercised in 1994 and 1995.
   The latest transaction brings USAir's total Boeing 737 orders to
68 aircraft, which will be delivered between now and 1992, plus 96
options, which would be delivered between 1992 and 1995.
   USAir, the nation's ninth-largest airline, plans to complete its
acquisition of Piedmont Aviation Inc. in August. USAir took
delivery of its first 737-300 in late 1984. It currently operates a
fleet of 56 737-300s.
   USAir also has ordered 20 Dutch Fokker 100 jets and holds
options on 20 more. First delivery is scheduled for June 1989.
USAir also recently signed a letter of intent with McDonnell
Douglas Corp. to purchase as many as 40 MD-82 aircraft.
</TEXT>
