<HEAD>Mesa Limited Partnership Reports First Quarter Earnings</HEAD>
<DATELINE>AMARILLO, Texas (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Citing declines in revenues from oil,
natural gas and condensate production, Mesa Limited Partnership
reported a net income of $14.6 million, or 15 cents per common
unit, on revenues of $105 million for the first quarter of 1989.
   Earnings for the same period a year earlier were $19.3 million,
or 17 cents per common unit, on revenues of $95 million.
   Gas production increased for the quarter, mostly because of the
addition of Tenneco Inc. properties acquired by Mesa last year, the
Amarillo-based partnership said Tuesday.
   Spot prices for natural gas were down because of the warm winter
weather, the partnership said.
