<FIRST>r f AM-AutoIncentives     04-25 0127</FIRST>
<SECOND>AM-Auto Incentives,0132</SECOND>
<HEAD>VW Offers U.S. Savings Bonds as Incentives</HEAD>
<DATELINE>TROY, Mich. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Volkswagen of America Inc. on Tuesday
announced an incentive program offering U.S. Savings Bonds to
people who buy or lease a new Volkswagen until May 31.
   The program offers buyers or leasers bonds ranging from $1,000
to $4,000 in face value, depending on the model chosen. For those
who don't want a bond, Volkswagen will contribute the purchase
price, generally half of the face value, toward the buyer's down
payment.
   The bonds, series EE, carry 6 percent interest rates and mature
in 10 to 12 years. No cash rebates are being offered, Volkswagen
spokesman Jay Amestoy said.
   Volkswagen of America is the U.S. marketing arm for the West
German automaker Volkswagen AG.
</TEXT>
